              <h2>Introduction</h2>

              <p>
                Planning a wedding is exciting — but for Muslim couples, it also
                comes with additional values, traditions, and sensitivities. A
                <strong>muslim wedding planner</strong> is someone who
                understands not just event logistics but also the religious,
                cultural, and ethical dimensions of a Nikah and Walima ceremony.
                In this guide, we'll walk you through everything — from when to
                hire one to how to get the most value — so your day is beautiful
                and halal.
              </p>

