              <h2>1. What Does a "Muslim Wedding Planner" Mean?</h2>

              <h3>1.1 Definition & Role</h3>
              <p>
                A <strong>muslim wedding planner</strong> is a wedding planner
                who:
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  Respects and incorporates Islamic etiquette (e.g. gender
                  separation, modesty, halal catering)
                </li>
                <li>
                  Understands Islamic wedding rituals (Nikah, Walima, Khutbah,
                  etc.)
                </li>
                <li>Balances cultural elements with religious guidelines</li>
                <li>
                  Acts as liaison between families, vendors, and religious
                  scholars
                </li>
              </ul>
              <p>
                They are more than event coordinators — they are guardians of
                the sanctity of your occasion.
              </p>

              <h3>1.2 Difference from a General Wedding Planner</h3>

